The paper deals with generative models (GANs) and meta-learning, which are both subfields of machine learning. Specifically, it focuses on image generation, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Reptile, a meta-learning algorithm, suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the subfields of neural networks (cs.NE) and graphics (cs.GR) due to its focus on deep learning and image generation. Overall, cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.CV (computer vision) are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
